Executive Profile
William Y. Tauscher  Executive Chairman, Blackhawk Network Holdings, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 6 different industries.See Board Relationships67$4,430,908As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. William Y. Tauscher, also known as Bill, serves as the President of L. Kee & Co Inc., a distributor of linens and bedding. Mr. Tauscher serves as the Chief Executive Officer of Likee & Company, a Chinese home textile manufacturer. Mr. Tauscher has been an Executive Chairman at Blackhawk Network Holdings, Inc. since August 2009. He served as Head of International & Corporate Development at Blackhawk Network Holdings, Inc. since February 2013 until August 30, 2016 ... and served as its Chief Executive Officer from August 2010 to February 22, 2016. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Blackhawk Network, Inc. since August 2010 to February 22, 2016. He serves as Chairman of the Board of Blackhawk Network, Inc. He served as Executive Chairman of Blackhawk Network, Inc. from March 2010 to August 2010 and as President from August 2010 to November 2010. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Vertical Communications, Inc. (formerly Artisoft Inc.) from September 2004 to May 17, 2011. Mr. Tauscher served as the President at Vertical Communications, Inc. from October 22, 2004 to November 2, 2009. Mr. Tauscher served as the Chief Executive Officer of MainStreet USA Corp., a marketing and technology e-commerce venture, from January 2000 to July 2000. Mr. Tauscher served as the Chief Executive Officer of Vanstar Corp. (formerly Computerland Corp.) since September 1988 until its acquisition by Inacom Corp. in February 1999. He served as the President of Vanstar Corp., from September 1988 to July 1995. Prior to Vanstar, Mr. Tauscher served as the Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and President of Foxmeyer Corp., a Wholesale Pharmaceutical and Beauty-Aid Distributor, Which was sold to National Intergroup in 1986. He formerly Blackhawk's executive chairman, has served as managing member of the Tauscher Group. Since 1999, Mr. Tauscher has also served on the executive team and board of several small enterprises during initial development of new technologies or periods of transition. Mr. Tauscher served as a Managing Member of The Tauscher Group, a private firm that invests and helps manage enterprises in home products, transportation, security and real estate. Mr. Tauscher has been the Executive Chairman of Vertical Communications Inc., since February 20, 2004. He served as the Chairman of Wanderport Corp. (known as Temtex Industries Inc.), since July 19, 2002. He served as Chairman of Vanstar Corp. from September 1987 to 1999. He has been Director of The Vons Companies, Inc. since 1987 and Blackhawk Network Holdings, Inc. since August 2007. He has been a Director of Temtex Industries Inc., since 2002. He served as a Director of InaCom Corp. He served as a Director of Safeway Inc. from May 12, 1998 to January 2015. He served as an Independent Director of Wanderport Corp. He served as a Director of Vanstar Corp. Mr. Tauscher holds a B.S. in Administrative Sciences from Yale University.Read Full Background




